Hard shell case included CA BUYERS MUST PAY CA SALES TAX Bill Tipton, a native Californian, was the printing-press machinist for the "San Diego Union Tribune” newspaper. A precision oriented man, and Bill's true love was making and repairing beautiful guitars in his woodshop garage behind his house in Carlsbad California. Under contract, he built several guitars for Wayne Charvel, whose company was bought by Fender guitars. Bill made only a few guitars Under his own name brand. Probably less than 50 guitars exist with his name on them. All of them are beautifully handcrafted and collaborated with inlays, and body work from other local craftsman and machinists, Bill's guitars never disappoint, and play like butter. They are each beautifully finished, with tremendous attention to detail. Bill made about 1 guitar per month. Handcrafted in the USA, his guitars rival Paul Reed Smith private stock, easily. If you win one, you will likely buy another.
